📁 .mvn/                                                 --> Maven wrapper files — ignore this for now (auto-generated)
📁src/                                                   --> ALL your code lives here
📁main/                                                  --> Your actual application code
📁java/com/taskmanager/                                  --> Your Java source files go here
📁controller/ you create                                 --> Handles HTTP requests — your "waiters"
📁service/ you create                                    --> Business logic — the "chef" deciding what to do
📁repository/ you create                                 --> Database queries — talks to MySQL
📁model/ you create                                      --> Your data objects (User, Task) — the "forms"
📁dto/ you create                                        --> Data Transfer Objects — what the API sends/receives
📁security/ you create                                   --> JWT + login config lives here
☕TaskManagerApiApplication.java auto-generated           --> The "main door" — this starts your app
📁resources/                                             --> Config files, not Java code
⚙️application.properties auto-generated                  --> Database URL, port, passwords go here
📁test/                                                  --> Test files go here — very important for companies
📄pom.xml auto-generated                                 --> The "shopping list" — lists all your dependencies

DTO means Data Transfer Object — it's just a simple container that holds the data coming IN from the user or going OUT to the user.
Think of it like a form.

src/main/java/com/taskmanager/
│
├── dto/
│   ├── RegisterRequest.java      ← what user sends to register
│   ├── LoginRequest.java         ← what user sends to login
│   └── AuthResponse.java         ← what we send back (the token)
│
├── security/
│   └── JwtUtil.java              ← creates and reads JWT tokens
│
├── service/
│   └── AuthService.java          ← business logic (hash password, check login)
│
└── controller/
    └── AuthController.java       ← the API endpoints (/register, /login)